args: I need to get out of here and report\nback to the main force before... Huh?!
Right-o! Think that about takes care of\nall the baddies around here.
Mopped 'em up but good, boss!\nLooks like you cleaned up all right, too.

All the enemies have been dealt with.
That being said, why would imperial
troops be hiding in an area like this
in the first place?
Intelligence gatherin', most likely.\nThey spy on us, then run back to mama\nif they see anything outta the ordinary.
But we sure took care'a that!
*yawn* Anyway, let's truss 'em up\nand go get ourselves some grub.
Aw, hell! Can't believe I fell for the ol'\n＂pretendin' to be unconscious＂ bit.\nGet back here, you!
Not likely, pal! I've got legs of lightning!
Damn, he IS fast! This punk's already\nput a wall between us and him!
*wheeze* Think I...lost 'em...\nNow to get back to base and—
She took the damn wall down!
That's the last bad guy down.

Can't believe you made a shortcut by
plowin' through some old ruin.
That's thinkin' outside the box—
or hell, outside the WALL!
Still, I'm certain my older brother\nwould have handled it even better.
Ain't no need to be modest here.\nStrut around! Ya earned it!
In that case, I will do so!
You're Mathias's father from the village!
Guy don't look like he's with the imperials,\nso what's he doin' here?
I was just bringing food to the soldiers\nand... Oh, dear Ilia. Please tell me you\ndidn't defeat them all!
Actually, yes—we did defeat them all.\nIs that a problem?
Sir, please explain what you mean.
The village elder needs to hear this.\nCome with me—we can explain\neverything once we arrive.

The hell's wrong with this place?
Not only were ya goin' along with
the imperials hidin' out in that ruin,
ya went and brought 'em FOOD!
We had no choice: Our village would have\nbeen razed to the ground had we tried to\ntake a stand against the Empire.
Ya coulda tried tellin' us about it!

And if we had told you? What then?
Likely you would have met the threat
with force, which could have led to
the exact same outcome.
I thought it better to submit to the Empire\nrather than resist and face certain death.
So what will you do now?
...Enough. Begone from here.\nThe matter does not concern you.
Hey, the boss is tryin' to HELP ya!
This village's future will be decided in\na discussion amongst its citizenry.\nI'm sorry, but I must insist that you leave.

No matter how good our intentions,
we're no better than the Empire if
we force them to bend to our will.
They deserve to make their own choice.
Can't say I much care for it,\nbut yer the boss, so...
Shake some dust, Sharena!\nWe're headin' back to the Halidom.

Yes, I know. It's just that... Well, I have
a friend named Mathias in this village,
and I was hoping to have a word with
him before I departed.
Should we wait for you outside\nthe village in that case?
No, please go on. It should be quick,\nso I'll just catch up to you later.
Gotcha. Don't be too long, yeah?
Gah! You again! ...Well, hell. I suppose\nthere's little point in hiding it now.

The soldiers in those ruins were under
orders to report back to the main force
on a regular basis. Now that you took
them all out, that can't happen.
And once they don't report back,\nthe main force will come here\nand wipe out the entire village.
Because that was always the agreement!\nAll they needed from us was to shut up\nand let the force in the ruins do its thing.

Now that they're gone, we have no purpose
at all. They'll brand us traitors and kill us
all as a lesson to everyone who would
think of standing against the Empire!

Yes! They surely WOULD! You think we're
the only village under the thumb of the
Empire? They'll sacrifice us to serve as
a warning to the rest of them!
It will be bad, bloody work. Young and old,\nman and woman... None will be spared.

If you'd left even ONE of those soldiers
standing in the ruins, we might have a
chance—but you and your merry band
went and took that from us!
I know you had good intentions, but...\nOh, damn it all! What are we to do?!
You will take every last person in the\nvillage and flee to the Halidom.\nWe can protect you there.
And what of the elderly? The children?\nThey'd never be able to keep up\non a march such as that.
Regardless, I'm going to return to the\nHalidom and speak to the prince. I know\nhe'll be able to come up with something.
ENOUGH already! You have done ENOUGH!\nPlease, I beg of you, stop meddling in our\naffairs and just...leave us be.
Do? There's nothing you can do.\nJust listen to the elder and go home.
Sharena, what were you and my father\ntalking about? What's going to happen?
...You are going to be fine, so put your\ncares away. I will find all the bad people\nand make sure they leave you be.
Of course! There is no foe I wont stand\nagainst if it means saving a friend!
Wait, is she going by HERSELF?
Oh no... I gotta do something!
